groups in Syria that are

15:01.100 --> 15:04.003 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
protected really by Turkey. So I
think this is something that's

15:04.036 --> 15:07.373 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
been brewing for some time. And
I think, on a broader point,

15:07.406 --> 15:10.243 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ever since the Russians began
the bombing campaign in Syria

15:10.276 --> 15:14.313 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and gave the U.S., for instance,
one hour's notice to get out of

15:14.347 --> 15:16.983 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the sky, there has been this
brinkmanship and there has been

15:17.016 --> 15:19.652 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the danger that something like
this would happen. And so I'm

15:19.685 --> 15:22.321 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
sure that the Turks in some
senses were just waiting for

15:22.355 --> 15:25.491 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
something like this to happen
and felt that they had to take a

15:25.525 --> 15:27.927 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
stance on this. JUDY WOODRUFF:
Nicholas Burns, if that's the

15:27.960 --> 15:32.265 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
case, if the Turks thought in
advance and in essence planned

15:32.298 --> 15:34.934 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to do this the next time a
Russian plane crossed their

15:34.967 --> 15:38.104 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
border, what does that say about
what the Turks are -- what their

15:38.137 --> 15:42.742 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
posture is at this point?
NICHOLAS BURNS: Well, I think

15:42.775 --> 15:45.711 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
President Obama got the balance
right today. He clearly backed

15:45.745 --> 15:48.748 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Turks on the legal issue of
protection of borders, but he

15:48.781 --> 15:52.251 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
also said that he would spend
all of his time trying now to

15:52.285 --> 15:55.154 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
de-escalate this conflict. And I
think what that means, Judy, is

15:55.188 --> 15:58.558 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that the United States is going
to be very active both in Moscow

15:58.591 --> 16:02.428 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and Ankara to counsel both to
stand down from any further

16:02.461 --> 16:05.798 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
