leadership. The Turks and

16:34.260 --> 16:36.729 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Russians clearly have not. And I
think it's the role of the

16:36.762 --> 16:39.732 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
United States to try to promote
that kind of transparency,

16:39.765 --> 16:43.369 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
because we don't want to see a
further incident like. Very

16:43.402 --> 16:46.739 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
dangerous. We haven't had
anything like this in nearly 60

16:46.772 --> 16:50.409 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
years in the NATO relationship
with both the Soviet Union and

16:50.443 --> 16:52.645 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Russia. JUDY WOODRUFF: Well,
before I ask you both about how

16:52.678 --> 16:56.148 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
