Hezbollah are there. That's

20:13.145 --> 20:15.681 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
another problem for the
Russians. They have a mainly

20:15.714 --> 20:19.952 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sunni Muslim population in their
own North Caucasus region, but

20:19.985 --> 20:22.488 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Russians have aligned
themselves with the Shia powers,

20:22.521 --> 20:25.925 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with Iran, with Hezbollah, and
with the Alawite regime in

20:25.958 --> 20:29.161 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Syria. And I think if the
Russians don't restrain the

20:29.195 --> 20:32.765 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Syrian government from firing
barrel bombs into civilian

20:32.798 --> 20:36.035 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
neighborhoods, the United States
ought to consider a no-flight

20:36.068 --> 20:38.938 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
zone with Turkey and other
